c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-18_"><p class="sc-gDGHff eHTxVX pf-19_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-21_">Work-related stress is often inevitable. In fact, you may perceive a certain level of pressure as motivating or beneficial. However, when stress levels become unmanageable, they become a problem that negatively affects productivity and health.
<br><br>The Workplace Health Report revealed that 76% of employees report moderate-to-high or high-stress levels. 33% report that high levels of stress impact productivity. The top cause of work-related stress is workload (73%), and 54% agree that the perfect amount of stress enables them to thrive.<br>
<br>In this article, we will discuss what stress is, its signs and symptoms, and how it negatively affects workplace productivity. We will also look at several coping mechanisms, including self-care tips, to help you manage stress at work.<br> 
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-22_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-24_">What is stress?
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-stress--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775094182.png?v=1680775097" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-stress--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775094182.png?v=1680775097 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-stress--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775094182_500x.png?v=1680775097 320w" width="1234" height="823" alt="What is stress? - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="What is stress? - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " style="aspect-ratio:1234 / 823" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-hmjpVf jFnkub pf-25_"/><p class="sc-gDGHff eHTxVX pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-28_">According to the World Health Organisation, stress is defined as:<br><br><i>“a state of worry or mental tension caused by a difficult situation. Stress is a natural human response that prompts us to address challenges and threats in our lives. Everyone experiences stress to some degree.”</i>
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-31_">Symptoms of stress
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/symptoms-of-stress--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775217741.png?v=1680775222" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/symptoms-of-stress--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775217741.png?v=1680775222 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/symptoms-of-stress--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775217741_500x.png?v=1680775222 320w" width="1840" height="1066" alt="Symptoms of stress - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Symptoms of stress - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " style="aspect-ratio:1840 / 1066" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-hmjpVf jFnkub pf-32_"/><p class="sc-gDGHff eHTxVX pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-35_">Stress can cause different symptoms that may significantly affect how you feel and behave physically and mentally. However, recognising when stress is why you think or act differently can be challenging.
<br><br>Stress may produce physical symptoms such as headaches or dizziness, muscle tension or pain, stomach problems, chest pain or a faster heartbeat, and sexual difficulties. Mental symptoms may include difficulty concentrating and/or making decisions, feeling overwhelmed, constant worry, and forgetfulness, among others.<br> 
<br>In addition, it is not uncommon for people to become irritable or snappy, sleep too little or too much, eat too little or too much, avoid certain places or people or drink or smoke more.
<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-36_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-38_">Stress in the workplace</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/stress-in-the-workplace--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775343915.png?v=1680775348" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/stress-in-the-workplace--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775343915.png?v=1680775348 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/stress-in-the-workplace--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775343915_500x.png?v=1680775348 320w" width="1969" height="1223" alt="Stress in the workplace - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Stress in the workplace - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " style="aspect-ratio:1969 / 1223" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-hmjpVf jFnkub pf-39_"/><p class="sc-gDGHff eHTxVX pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-42_">Workplace stress can be defined as the harmful physical and emotional responses that occur when the job requirements do not match the individual's capabilities, resources, or needs. 
<br><br>Team members who are feeling work-related stress may start acting differently. They may eat more or less than usual, smoke, drink or take drugs to cope or have difficulty sleeping at night.<br>
<br>Talking to someone like your line manager is vital if you feel stressed at work. This will enable them a chance to help you and stop the situation from worsening.<br>
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-45_">What are the effects of stress in the workplace?</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-the-effects-of-stress-in-the-workplace--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775454826.png?v=1680775463" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-the-effects-of-stress-in-the-workplace--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775454826.png?v=1680775463 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-the-effects-of-stress-in-the-workplace--the-mandatory-training-group-uk--1680775454826_500x.png?v=1680775463 320w" width="1304" height="853" alt="What are the effects of stress in the workplace? - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="What are the effects of stress in the workplace? - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " style="aspect-ratio:1304 / 853" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-hmjpVf jFnkub pf-46_"/><p class="sc-gDGHff eHTxVX pf-47_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-49_">People respond differently to stress. What stresses one person may not stress another. Skills, experience, age, or disability can all negatively impact a worker's ability to cope with stress.
